sourceList.expandedForm: SNOMED Multiaxial coding - an alphanumeric string that includes hyphens, parentheses, and sometimes ellipses.
SNOMED Hospital Formulary Code - the American Hospital Formulary Code for a chemical contained in SNOMED International (e.g. 84:24:12)

SNOMED International subset indicator - valid values: * =can code using two T codes or G code for laterality B Bethesda system (Morphology); IC= ICDO (Oncology) related; N=Nursing; N* =Nursing, provisional; U=Ultrastructure (Morphology); V= Veterinary; V* =Veterinary AND can code using two T codes or G code for laterality (Topography)
Enzyme Commission Number - International Union of Biochemists Enzyme Commission number for an enzyme concept.
SNOMED ICD9CM Reference - the ICD9CM code or codes listed as relevant to the meaning of the concept in SNOMED International.
